chunks:
Biology 101: Cellular Respiration Key Concepts: Mitochondria, ATP, Glycolysis, Krebs Cycle, Electron Transport Chain

1. Overview
Cellular respiration is the process by which cells convert glucose and oxygen into ATP (adenosine triphosphate), the cell's energy currency.

Equation: C6H12O6 + 6O2 → 6CO2 + 6H2O + ATP

2. Stages of Cellular Respiration
a. Glycolysis
• Occurs in the cytoplasm
• Breaks 1 glucose molecule into 2 pyruvate molecules
• Produces 2 ATP and 2 NADH

b. Krebs Cycle
• Takes place in mitochondrial matrix
• Generates 2 ATP, 6 NADH, and 2 FADH2 per glucose
